news.title: Nagpur civic body collects Rs 97.42 crore property tax during Apr-Sept 2021
news.para: Property tax department’s poor performance continued. To stay abreast with the target of Rs289.43 crore, NMC should have generated Rs144.71 crore, but created only Rs97.42 crore.

news.title: Goa: Sand mining in Chapora river can resume in four zones
news.para: SEIAA has asked for further scientific studies to be carried out in the case of two other zones in the Chapora. Applications were received from the North Goa collector for six zones in the river for sand mining.

news.title: Noida will soon acquire land for Delhi-Mumbai expressway-airport link
news.para: On October 12, the National Highways Authority of India had asked the district administration to start work on acquiring private land chunks on its behalf.

news.title: Complete deficient DLF-3 infrastructure work by year-end: Haryana CM
news.para: In the next two weeks, MCG will conduct a survey of deficient infrastructure in the colony, prepare an estimate of the funds required to complete pending works, if any, and submit it to DLF.

news.title: New policy for power supply to private colonies in Gurugram
news.para: DHBVN had stopped issuing new electricity connections to property owners in colonies developed by 16 builders as they are yet to pay the discom infrastructure charges amounting to over Rs 317 crore.

news.title: Starwood Capital raises $10 billion for latest real estate fund
news.para: The fundraise for Starwood Distressed Opportunity Fund XII exceeded the $7.6 billion it had raised for a similar fund in 2018, the company said.

news.title: Chinese developer Xinyuan avoids default, lending curbs loosen
news.para: Xinyuan said that holders of more than 90% of the company's $229 million notes due Oct. 15 had agreed to the exchange, which would see it deliver new bonds worth $205.4 million and $19.1 million cash.

news.title: Evergrande's CEO in Hong Kong for restructuring, asset sale talks: Sources
news.para: CEO Xia Haijun, a confidant of chairman Hui Ka Yan and who runs Evergrande's day-to-day operations including financing, has been in Hong Kong, where the property firm has a major presence, for more than two months, the two sources told Reuters.

news.title: China Properties defaults on notes worth $226 million
news.para: China Properties said it had failed to secure funds by Oct. 15, the maturity date of the notes, due to a "timing mismatch" and that it would not be able to make repayments until it had sold or refinanced some of its assets.

news.title: Evergrande's $1.7 billion Hong Kong headquarters' sale flops: Sources
news.para: Yuexiu, based in the southern city of Guangzhou, was close to sealing a deal in August to acquire the 26-storey China Evergrande Centre in Hong Kong's Wan Chai district that serves as Evergrande's local headquarters, said the sources.

news.title: China's President calls for progress on property tax in drive for prosperity
news.para: Such a tax could curb rampant speculation in the housing market, which is currently under intense global scrutiny as developer China Evergrande Group (3333.HK) struggles with a debt crisis.

news.title: Singapore: ESR-REIT to buy ARA LOGOS for $1 billion
news.para: The combined ESR-LOGOS REIT will hold a portfolio of business parks, logistics, warehouse and industrial properties with total assets of about S$5.4 billion in Singapore and Australia.

news.title: Gurugram chokes on dust from its own infrastructure sites
news.para: The graded response action plan (GRAP) was supposed to come into effect on Friday, but hasn’t been imposed so far as the government hasn’t received any directions from the Commission for Air Quality Management.

news.title: Kanjurmarg land is for affordable housing, not Mumbai metro: Garodia family
news.para: The letter dated December 3, 2020, said the Garodias have been the lessee of about 500 acres of land since the past several decades. It includes about 249 acres within the limits of village Kanjur (Jenkins Salt Works) and village Bhandup and another 251 acres of marsh land of village Kanjur (Arthur Salt Works).

news.title: CAQM asks Noida Authority to take action against pollution violations
news.para: While construction dust was the problem in most areas, other problems included transportation of uncovered construction material, repetitive digging of roads by telecom companies, road repair with material lying uncovered and no water sprinkling at construction sites.
